list.name: Alarms On
list.rawQuery:
SELECT
  extract(epoch from ts) AS time,
  (a.name  ||'  @ '|| c.name || ' changed to ' || value)::varchar  as text,
  (a.name || ',' || c.name || ',' || value)::varchar  as tags
FROM historical_event
INNER JOIN historical_alarm AS a ON a.id = (meta->'alarm')::integer
INNER JOIN cold_rooms_coldroom AS c ON c.id = (meta->'cold_room')::integer
WHERE $__timeFilter(ts) AND a.name = '${alarm:raw}'  AND c.name = '${coldRoom:raw}' AND type='AlarmEvent' AND value = 'true'
ORDER BY time DESC
LIMIT 100

targets.rawSql:
WITH RECURSIVE params (POINTS, Ts, ts_from, ts_to, cold_room, measurement, bucket_time) as (
	VALUES (400, INTERVAL '0.5 sec',
	  -- now(), now() - INTERVAL '1 min',
	  $__timeTo()::timestamptz, $__timeFrom()::timestamptz,
	  (SELECT id FROM cold_rooms_coldroom WHERE name='${coldRoom:raw}'),
	  (SELECT id FROM historical_measurement WHERE name='${floatMeasurement:raw}'),
	  INTERVAL '0 sec'
	)
	UNION ALL
	SELECT POINTS, Ts, ts_from, ts_to, cold_room, measurement, GREATEST(
		 (ts_from - ts_to) / (POINTS - 1), Ts
	)
	FROM params WHERE bucket_time = INTERVAL '0 sec'
)
SELECT q.* FROM (
  SELECT
  	time_bucket(bucket_time, d.ts) AS time,
  	-- $__timeFrom()::timestamptz as from, $__timeTo()::timestamptz as to,
  	avg(d.value) as value, min(d.value), max(d.value)
  	-- avg(d.value) - stddev_pop(d.value) as lower_sigma,
  	-- avg(d.value) + stddev_pop(d.value) as upper_sigma
  	-- stddev(d.value), count(d.*)
   FROM historical_floatmeasurementdata as d, params
  WHERE bucket_time > INTERVAL '0 sec'
    AND cold_room_id = cold_room 
    AND measurement_id = measurement
    AND d.ts BETWEEN ts_to AND ts_from
  GROUP BY time
  ORDER BY time DESC
  LIMIT 400
) as q
-- necessary to prevent 'data outside time range' message
WHERE $__timeFilter(q.time)

WITH RECURSIVE params (POINTS, Ts, ts_from, ts_to, cold_room, measurement, bucket_time) as (
	VALUES (400, INTERVAL '0.5 sec',
	  $__timeTo()::timestamptz, $__timeFrom()::timestamptz,
	  (SELECT id FROM cold_rooms_coldroom WHERE name='${coldRoom:raw}'),
	  (SELECT id FROM historical_measurement WHERE name='${integerMeasurement:raw}'),
	  INTERVAL '0 sec'
	)
	UNION ALL
	SELECT POINTS, Ts, ts_from, ts_to, cold_room, measurement, GREATEST(
		 (ts_from - ts_to) / (POINTS - 1), Ts
	)
	FROM params WHERE bucket_time = INTERVAL '0 sec'
)
SELECT q.* FROM (
  SELECT
  	time_bucket(bucket_time, d.ts) AS time,
  	avg(d.value) as value, min(d.value), max(d.value)
   FROM historical_integermeasurementdata as d, params
  WHERE bucket_time > INTERVAL '0 sec'
    AND cold_room_id = cold_room 
    AND measurement_id = measurement
    AND d.ts BETWEEN ts_to AND ts_from
  GROUP BY time
  ORDER BY time DESC
  LIMIT 400
) as q
-- necessary to prevent 'data outside time range' message
WHERE $__timeFilter(q.time)

SELECT
  $__time(ts),
  m.name as metric,
  value::integer
FROM historical_booleanmeasurementdata
INNER JOIN cold_rooms_coldroom As c ON c.id = cold_room_id
INNER JOIN historical_measurement As m ON m.id = measurement_id
WHERE $__timeFilter(ts) AND c.name = '${coldRoom:raw}' AND m.name = '${booleanMeasurement:raw}'
ORDER BY 1
